Package com.foreach.across.core.convert

Class StringToDateTimeConverter

java.lang.Object
com.foreach.across.core.convert.StringToDateTimeConverter
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.springframework.core.convert.converter.ConditionalConverter, org.springframework.core.convert.converter.ConditionalGenericConverter, org.springframework.core.convert.converter.GenericConverter
public class StringToDateTimeConverter extends Object implements org.springframework.core.convert.converter.GenericConverter, org.springframework.core.convert.converter.ConditionalGenericConverter
Default converter that tries a long list of default patterns for parsing a String back to a Date or a TemporalAccessor for a fixed (default: US) locale. This converter is registered by default when the AcrossContext creates a ConversionService.

A blank string is considered to be a null date but will not result in a conversion exception.

Author:
Arne Vandamme
